Package de.muspellheim.commons.sql

Class ResultSetMapper<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.muspellheim.commons.sql.ResultSetMapper<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the entity type.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConstructorResultSetMapper, SetterResultSetMapper
    public abstract class ResultSetMapper<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Mapping a result set to an entity.

    Use static methods to map individual columns or one of the sub classes ConstructorResultSetMapper or SetterResultSetMapper to map a whole entity.

    Column labels are mapped to property names by following convention: a column label with snake case is mapped to a property name with camel case. For example the column label day_of_birth is mapped to property name dayOfBirth.

    Default registered column mappers exists for:

    • String
    • Long/long
    • Integer/int
    • Short/short
    • Byte/byte
    • Double/double
    • Float/float
    • Boolean/boolean
    • byte[]
    • LocalDate
    • LocalTime
    • LocalDateTime
    • Instant
    See Also:
    ConstructorResultSetMapper, SetterResultSetMapper
